channel.title: Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States - New items on govinfo
channel.description: Provides access to newly published GovInfo content from the Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States. The Public Papers of the Presidents, which is compiled and published by the Office of the Federal Register, National Archives and Records Administration (NARA), is an official collection of Presidential writings,

image.title: Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States - New items on govinfo

channel.copyright: Title 17, Section 105, United States Code, provides that: Copyright protection under this title is not available for any work of the United States Government, but the United States Government is not precluded from receiving and holding copyrights transferred to it by assignment, bequest, or otherwise. For more information, see https://www.govinfo.gov/about/policies#copyright
